\hat\beta
x_i
 \beta^2 + \beta x_i = y_i  
 \varepsilon_i = \beta^2 + \beta x_i - y_i \\ \frac{1}{2}\frac{\partial}{\partial x_i}\sum \varepsilon_i^2 = \sum \varepsilon_i \beta = 0 \\ -\frac{1}{2}\frac{\partial}{\partial y_i}\sum \varepsilon_i^2 = \sum \varepsilon_i = 0 \\ \Rightarrow \qquad \hat\beta_{1/2}=-\frac{\langle x\rangle}{2}\pm \sqrt{\frac{\langle x \rangle}{4}+\langle y \rangle} 
